  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Asset Context&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    There are multiple elements for describing the context of an asset, as listed in the image below. This image focuses on&#xD;
    describing the usage context, which is the set of elements that must be described and understood for the asset to be&#xD;
    successfully used: development environment, runtime environment, reuse scope, target asset consumer, business domain,&#xD;
    process location for reuse, architecture location for reuse, dependencies and relationships to other assets, interfaces&#xD;
    provided&amp;nbsp;and consumed, services provided and consumed, policies compliance.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img height=&quot;337&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/assetcontext2.gif&quot; width=&quot;569&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.mgmt.asset_based_dev.base-ibm/guidances/concepts/well_formed_asset_768653EE.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_vI2YEPD5Edq7ls4zEErftg&quot;>Well-Formed Asset&lt;/a> describes as many of these elements, and others,&amp;nbsp;that&#xD;
    describe the context for the asset to be successfully be reused.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
